### Human:
Before Cam broke his right arm, he was able to type 9 words per minute on his phone.  After he broke his arm, he had to use his left hand for a while, and he could only type 6 words per minute. What is the difference between the number of words he could type in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm
### Assistant:

The average number of words Cam typed per minute with both hands was 9. 
After breaking his right arm, Cam used his left hand for a while and could only type 6 words per minute. So the total number of words Cam typed in 5 minutes after breaking his arm is (6*5) = 30 words. 
Before breaking his arm, Cam could type 9 words per minute with both hands, so he could type (9*5) = 45 words in 5 minutes before breaking his arm. Therefore, there was a difference of (45-30) = 15 words between the number of words Cam typed in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm.
